============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is the internet?
A1: The internet is a global network of interconnected
     computers using TCP/IP protocols. It began as ARPANET
     in 1969 and became public with the World Wide Web in
     1994.

Q2: What is the Magna Carta?
A2: The Magna Carta (1215) was a charter limiting royal
     power in England, establishing that the king is subject
     to law. It influenced modern constitutional law and
     human rights.

Q3: What is machine learning?
A3: Machine learning enables systems to learn from
     experience without being explicitly programmed, using
     data to improve performance automatically.

Q4: What is inflation?
A4: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

Q5: What is capitalism?
A5: Capitalism is an economic system where private
     individuals own the means of production and markets
     determine prices and production through supply and
     demand.

============================================================
  MATHEMATICS
============================================================

Theorem/Law:  Prime Number Theorem
Branch:       Number Theory
Formula:      π(n) ~ n/ln(n)
Applications: Cryptography, algorithm analysis
Discoverer:   Hadamard/de la VP (1896)

Theorem/Law:  Law of Large Numbers
Branch:       Probability
Formula:      Sample mean converges to expected value
Applications: Insurance, gambling, statistics
Discoverer:   Jacob Bernoulli (1713)

Theorem/Law:  Four Color Theorem
Branch:       Topology
Formula:      Any planar map needs at most 4 colors
Applications: Cartography, graph coloring
Discoverer:   Appel and Haken (1976)

